@731 = ~Ghost Weapon~
@732 = ~Ghost Weapon (Evocation)
Level: 3
Range: 0
Duration: 3 rounds/2 levels
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: special
Saving Throw: none

The warlord that run out of weapons can create one with the spell Ghost Weapon. This spell creates in the hand of the mage a portion of ether that he can mold to give it the shape of a weapon he masters. After that the weapon can not leave his hand throughout the duration of the spell, unless replaced by another weapon shaped the same way. Such a weapon has damage points doubled (a ghost long sword therefore inflits 2D8 damage points per hit) and a better penetration, for a +2 THAC0 bonus. The ghost weapon also inflicts 6 additional damage points to undead that are particularly vulnerable to it.

Note: Do not create a two-handed sword or a halberd if you are equipped with a shield; this inconsistency would crash the game. If you want such a weapon, then take under consideration to unequip your shield first.~
