The search for an unstoppable hit led the warlord to create this spell. It makes appear in the air a sword forged of pure wild magic that inevitably hits the designated target and inflicts 1D8 damage. Moreover, while hitting the sword generates one of the following:
- 2D8 points of damage
- 4D8 points of damage
- Paralysis for 2D4 rounds if a saving throw vs. spells is failed, 1D3 rounds if saving throw is successful

Starting from level 12, the warlord controls a little better the spell and can influence the chaotic magic that drives the sword to add more violent or other elemental random effects:
- 6D8 points of fire damage
- 8D8 points of cold damage
- Dispel Magic (no saving throw)
- Flesh to Stone if a saving throw vs. petrification is failed with a -2 bonus, otherwise paralysis for 2D4 rounds
- 10D8 points of electricity damage.~
